Abba Kabir Yusuf, son-in-law to Rabiu Musa Kwankwaso, has been declared governorship candidate of the New Nigeria Peoples Party (NNPP) in Kano state. In a primary held at the Sani Abacha youth centre on Monday, Musa Bako Aujara, the party’s election committee chairman, said Yusuf is the only aspirant that contested the NNPP governorship ticket in the state. Musa said a total of 1,452 delegates participated in the exercise, with three from each of the 484 wards, adding that all the delegates affirmed Yusuf as the party’s candidate. “Going by the party guidelines, you can affirm a candidate through the use of ballot and there is only one contestant in this exercise in the person of Abba Yusuf,” he said “I am chairing the committee organising this exercise along with four other members, that include Dr. Sani Ado, Bashir Yusuf, Abubakar Sulaiman, and one other member. “Meanwhile, there were a total of 1,452 delegates to vote in this exercise as there are three delegates from each of the 484 wards in Kano.”